metadata.dc:description: Swyer's syndrome is a pure gonadal dysgenesis with female external genitalia. A likely complication is the appearance of tumour's dysgenetic gonads. This paper studies a case report of gonadoblastoma in a female patient with this syndrome.
metadata.dc:title: Gonadoblastoma en un síndrome de Swyer.
[Gonadoblastoma in Swyer syndrome].
